com.sri.kernel.modules
Class ModuleInfo

java.lang.Object
  com.sri.kernel.modules.ModuleInfo
public class ModuleInfo
extends java.lang.Object

This is the main data structure to encapsulate a module. All a modules information is stored in this class, including a reference to the actual module.

Version:
1.5
Author:
Joseph Monti, Smart Robots

isLoaded

public boolean isLoaded()
This will determine if the module is loaded or not. If it is loaded, true will be returned.

Returns:
True if module has been loaded, false otherwise.

loadModule

public void loadModule(Module module)
This is used when a module is loaded. It loads the module into the ModuleInfo. This is synonomous with setModule(Module module).

Parameters:
module - The module.

unloadModule

public void unloadModule()
This is used when the module is unloaded. It removes the reference to the actual module so it can be cleaned by the Garbage Collector and will be considered unloaded.
